reddam suom sibi, ‘ I will restore to him his own,' i.e. the treasure. We should expect ei not sibi. But suom draws the dat. into its neigh- bourhood and makes it reflexive. So often in the Comedians suom sibi and the like, e.g. Pers. 81 sua sibi pecunia hodie illam faciat leno libertam suam, Poen. 1083 suam sibi rem saluam sistam. See Roby, L. G. 1143 and 2265.
